pre-requisite:
go
nodejs
npm
geth (ln -s $PATH/build/bin/geth /usr/local/bin)
bootnode (ln -s $PATH/build/bin/bootnoode /usr/local/bin)
truffle (npm install -g truffle)
solc (npm install -g solc)
jq (apt-get install jq)
sudo apt install sleuthkit

sudo apt install jq (for parsing json object in bash)




Setup geth and bootnode.

boot.key is generated using "bootnode -genkey boot.key"

Run nodesetup.sh bash script. This will setup 3 nodes.

Expose port for node1 (30311):
rpc : 8501

for node2 (30312):
rpc : 8502

for node3 (30313):
rpc : 8503


Deploying smart contract using truffle:
Truffle v4.1.14 (core: 4.1.14)
Solidity v0.4.24 (solc-js)

sudo npm install -g truffle 
sudo npm install -g solc
mkdir truffle 
cd truffle
truffle init

Steps:
./setupnodes
deploy contract 
changes contract address in app and time 
run node app.js 


